Out southbank apartment was ideally located right across the bridge from downtown. My first taste of public transportation and non-stop traveling.

properties.name: Budget Inn
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21 North lima, ohYup, I lived in a hotel room with my parents and my brother for about 4 months, until we found a location for the family restaurant. I had just moved to the midwest from Cali. What culture shock. I started school there, only to moved again to a new school 9 weeks into the school years. Talk about uprooting. I\'m not quite sure those where happy times...

properties.name: Campus West Townhomes
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21allendale, miMan, what a sham those places were. College housing that somehow restricted college parties. What was the point then? Well, I did tons of maturing here. Like how not to go on a shopping spree with financial aid that is supposed to go towards rent. Still, lots of good times with friends.

properties.name: Erik's Parents
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21 cedar springs, miYes, we moved in with his parents. But only until we moved away to go to grad school, I swear... Actually, we lived there a short while. It was interesting living in some one else\'s home. As much as I appreciated the help, I don\'t want to do that again. I enjoy the freedom to do what I please in my own home.

properties.name: High School Years in the Midwest
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21 calcutta, ohThis nastyfied-shag-carpet-1950\'s house was my home until I escaped to college at 17yo. I somehow only remember gloomy winters and humid summers while living here. Oh, and working at the restaurant, lying in order to go to high school parties, being a prisoner of my age, and longing for sunny Cal. I actually would save my tips and hide it behind picture frames, as my stash to go head to CA as soon as I turned 18. How dramatic teenagers can be...

properties.name: In class
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21allendale, miI went home right after my first class because my roommate/classmate forgot her text book at home. When I first saw some of the footage, I thought how could both towers be on fire at the same time. I was so confused. I somehow thought I should go to class. When I got out of my second class, my boyfriend at the time was waiting for me outside to tell me that he had heard on TV at work that one plane crashed in Pittsburgh. My parents where living there at the time. I tried to keep it together as I rushed home and to call my mom. When she answered and I told her why I was so upset, she just gave me a nervous laugh. I was quite perturbed that the news would say Pittsburgh, when in actuallity, it was more like 30 miles outside of Pittsburgh. I will never forget how scared and vulnerable I was that day.

properties.name: My Big City Home
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21chicago, ilI love my Chicago apartment living. Granted, I miss having my own garage to park my car, not having someone live below or above me, not having my hallway stink, not getting my car broken into, or not having to carry all my groceries up at once. But I love living in the city. You can always find something to do here. I just love it. I\'m going to miss it...

properties.name: My Parent's House
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21 holland, miYes, we then moved in with my parents. And then we moved into our own place. Erik and I drove like 30 mins. to get to work. But in the summer, who cares. I miss my mom...

properties.name: The Duplex
properties.description: Posted by Missdi21allendale, miThe Jordan St. Duplex. Wow, what a place. Good rent, good place to throw parties, friends lived in the other half, and Erik & my first place together. Our friends still talk about how awesome this place was. Oh, and did I forget that it was on the way back from the beach, hence pink drinks, hence Edward-40-hands-parties. *insert sigh here*
